sql:
SELECT AVG(attendance) AS average_attendance
FROM games
WHERE home_team_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
A "completed" game refers to a game that has finished and is no longer in progress or scheduled for a later time.; 
Participating in more than one game implies that a team has played at least two games.; 
Average attendance is calculated by summing up the attendance of all games played by a team and dividing it by the total number of games played.

- In sports, particularly football (soccer), the team with the most points at the end of the season is typically declared the winner; 
- Points are usually awarded as 3 points for a win, 1 point for a tie, and 0 points for a loss; 
- Goal difference is calculated by subtracting the number of goals conceded from the number of goals scored, serving as a tiebreaker if teams have the same number of points; 
- The team with the higher goal difference is considered to be performing better.
